-- Shares in Scottish-based banks open lower on independence fears
-- By Matt Scuffham
-- Mon Sep 08, 2014 03:10AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Sept 8 (Reuters) - Shares in Scottish-based banks opened lower on Monday after supporters of Scottish independence took their first opinion poll lead since the referendum campaign began. [ID:nL5N0R70TX]

Shares in Lloyds Banking Group <LLOY.L> were down 2.3 percent in early trading with Royal Bank of Scotland <RBS.L> shares down 2.1 percent. Scotland will decide on Sept. 18 whether to stay in the United Kingdom.